      "agent_response": {
        "response_text": "The schema has 11 tables. Based on the models and the existing migration, here's the tenancy plan:\n\n**Tables requiring `tenant_id`** (8 of 11):\n- `users`, `organizations`, `invoices`, `subscriptions`, `audit_logs`, `api_keys`, `webhooks`, `feature_flags`\n\n**Tables that are global** (no tenancy needed):\n- `plans`, `countries`, `currency_rates`\n\n**Migration strategy:**\n1. Add `tenant_id UUID NOT NULL` to all 8 tables\n2. Backfill from `organizations.id` via FK join\n3. Add composite indexes: `(tenant_id, id)` on each table\n4. Add row-level security policies in PostgreSQL\n5. Update all FK constraints to include `tenant_id`\n\nI'll start with the migration SQL and model updates.",
