        "response_text": "Created two files:\n\n**`002_add_tenancy.sql`** — adds `tenant_id UUID NOT NULL DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()` to 8 tables, backfills from `organizations.id`, then drops the DEFAULT constraint so future inserts must supply it explicitly. Adds composite indexes and FK constraints.\n\n**`rls_policies.sql`** — enables RLS on all 8 tables and adds policies:\n```sql\nCREATE POLICY tenant_isolation ON invoices\n  USING (tenant_id = current_setting('app.tenant_id')::uuid);\n```\n\n**`models.py`** — added `tenant_id = models.UUIDField()` to all 8 models with `db_index=True`.\n\nNext: apply the migration and run the test suite.",
